## 2. INJECTION PARAMETERS

### 2.1 Volumes and Flow Rates

| Study | Volume | Flow Rate | Needle Gauge | Species |
|--------------|--------------|--------------|-----------------|--------------|
| **Hirabayashi et al., 2024** | 2-3 μl/site | 0.1 μl/min | 30G | Macaque (OFC) |
| **Sano et al., 2020** | 0.1-0.5 μl/site | 0.1 μl/min | Not specified | Mouse (various) |
| **Noritake et al., 2023** | 0.5-0.75 μl | Not specified | Not specified | Macaque (MPFC/LH) |
| **Ohta et al., 2021** | 1-10 μl | 1 μl/min | Not specified | Macaque |
| **Miura et al., 2020** | 100-500 nl | 100 nl/min | 35G | Mouse (insula) |
| **Gerits et al., 2015** | 23-920 nl | Not specified | Not specified | Macaque |
| **Kinoshita et al., 2012** | 0.5 ml (spinal) | 0.1 ml/min | 100 μm tip | Macaque (C6-T1) |
| **Kinoshita et al., 2019** | 0.5-0.8 μl | Not specified | Not specified | Macaque (SC/Pul) |

**Recommended Practices:** - **Small volumes (100-500 nl)** for focal
targeting in mice - **Larger volumes (1-3 μl)** for primate cortex with
broader spread - **Slow flow rates (0.1-1 μl/min)** minimize tissue
damage and backflow - **30-35G needles** for mice; **27-30G** for NHPs

### 2.2 Expression Times

| Study | Expression Time | Notes |
|-----------------|--------------------------------------|-----------------|
| **Hirabayashi et al., 2024** | 7 weeks | DREADD expression verified by PET |
| **Kinoshita et al., 2019** | 6-11 weeks | Tet-On system; Dox effects at 10 days |
| **Trautmann et al., 2021** | 5 weeks | GCaMP6f expression in motor cortex |
| **Tremblay et al., 2020** | 4-12 weeks | Typical range across NHP studies |
| **Sano et al., 2020** | 3-4 weeks | AAV-mediated retrograde labeling |

**General Guidelines:** - **Minimum 3-4 weeks** for AAV expression -
**6-8 weeks** optimal for most NHP optogenetics - **10-12+ weeks** may
be needed for some serotypes/promoters

